The paper deals with the segmentation and classification of animals from camera-trap images using machine learning techniques such as Multi-Layer Robust Principal Component Analysis (RPCA), Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator (LASSO), and Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) or Support Vector Machines (SVM). These techniques are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
